Altoros Log Search for Pivotal Platform is a flexible combination of Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana (ELK)
that provides log aggregation and parsing algorithms for Pivotal Platform operators and developers. 
The solution provides shared service plan. Pivotal Platform operators can create a 
Log Search cluster, where access will be shared within a group of developers. 

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

The Altoros Log Search for Pivotal Platform provides role-based access to system and application logs.
Out-the-box, users get:

+ Retrieving and parsing of logs received from Pivotal Platform
+ Secure authorized access to these logs in Kibana
+ Useful dashboards and search queries to start log analysis
+ Shared service plan


## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

Altoros Log Search for Pivotal Platform includes the following key features:

* **Pivotal Platform logs**: Collecting logs from all Pivotal Platform components
* **Services logs**: Provides the ability to collect logs from all Pivotal Platform Data Services available on Pivotal Network
* **Application logs**: Log Search is configured to get all application logs by default
* **SSO and multi-tenancy**: Uses the Cloud Foundry UAA service to control access to Kibana dashboards based on user role and rights within the platform. Multi-tenancy is implemented according to the roles defined by Cloud Foundry UAA.
* **Dashboards and visualization**: Provides out-of-the-box Dashboards for application and Pivotal Platform platform logs
* **Automated back-ups**: Users can setup automated backups and the archiving of logs to any S3-compatible storage system 

